      "content": "The thought that your presence is harming their happiness is a painful symptom of your own trauma, not a prediction of the future, and it is a mistake to believe you can cure them by disappearing. Healing is rarely linear, and the fact that you are struggling means you are still fighting for a better outcome, which is your love speaking through the chaos. If you feel you are the only one holding everything together, that is a heavy burden to carry alone, but therapists and support groups are designed to help parents find stability without losing themselves.",
